ABOUT:
This is a port of the OpenBSD hal for atheros device drivers that is
source-compatible with the Madwifi driver for linux.


DOWNLOAD:
Get up to date sources from:
http://pdos.csail.mit.edu/~jbicket/openhal/

BUILDING: 
To build with Madwifi, place the Openhal source directory in the
Madwifi directory. Now edit Makefile.inc and set the following:

HAL=${DEPTH}/openhal
ATH_HAL=${DEPTH}/openhal

After this, go to the top directory and build like you normally would. 


编译需要hal目录下的两个子目录，以包含OS的头文件和需要的平台文件
